<h1>About Pusat Kraftangan Sabah</h1>

<p>
To foster cultural diversity through craft-making and skills training,
preserving heritage while creating sustainable livelihoods.
</p>

<p>
PKS features a two-storey building with the ground floor dedicated to
exhibitions and retail of handicraft products including textiles,
batik, rattan, bamboo, ceramics and glassware.
</p>

<p>
Visitors can explore the Textile Gallery, Handicraft Gallery and
Digital Gallery while observing artisans at work and participating
in hands-on workshops such as batik painting and weaving.
</p>

